    "analysis": "We have completed global-threshold calculation and incident-window filtering. Metric analysis shows widespread socket KPI breaches across many services starting ~2024-01-20T21:31:00Z, plus isolated strong memory/diskio spikes on 'user' and rabbitmq-exporter. Log analysis shows no error messages in error_logs and most log.error_count values equal P95 (zeros), while several services (session-db, front-end, catalogue, queue-master, payment, orders, user, shipping, carts-db) show spikes in log.row_count (traffic) in the window. Traces are empty. Because many services show socket anomalies simultaneously, the pattern is consistent with a network/socket-level problem, but we must select a root-cause service from the allowed list (carts, catalogue, orders, payment, user). To disambiguate, we need a compact severity ranking restricted to those allowed services that compares how strongly their KPIs deviated from global P95 (not just count of equals-to-threshold). Current aggregates show that 'user' has isolated but high-memory/diskio breaches and a moderate number of socket anomalies starting later, while 'payment' and 'orders' have socket breaches across the window but with little deviation above threshold. The next step is to produce a focused summary of anomaly severity for only the allowed components across key KPIs (cpu, mem, diskio, socket, workload) so we can identify which allowed service shows the most significant deviation and earliest fault occurrence.",
  "completed": "False",
  "instruction": "Using metric.csv, restrict to components in the candidate list ['carts','catalogue','orders','payment','user']. For each (cmdb_id, kpi_name) in that set:\n1) Compute global P95 of 'value' using the full series for that group.\n2) Filter points to the incident window 2024-01-20 21:28:56 UTC → 2024-01-20 21:58:56 UTC.\n3) Find points in the window where value >= global P95. For each group return one compact row with columns: cmdb_id, kpi_name, global_p95, anomaly_count_in_window, earliest_anomaly_timestamp_utc (ISO), max_value_in_window, severity_ratio. Define severity_ratio = (max_value_in_window - global_p95) / (global_p95 if global_p95>0 else max(1, max_value_in_window)) so it is comparable when threshold is zero. If no anomalies for a group, omit it. Return up to 20 rows sorted by severity_ratio desc, then anomaly_count_in_window desc. Keep output compact; do not print full time series." }

